ChatGPT said:

Perfect 👌 I got it clearly.
You want:

✅ Left & right arrows (clickable)
✅ There’s a progress line divided into 5 equal parts (since you have total 8 slides and show 4 at once → you get 2 full views → but you want 5 steps, so it changes a bit per slide)
✅ Each click (next/prev) moves the Swiper and updates the bold/filled portion of that progress line

Let’s make that happen — here’s the full working version 👇

jsx
"use client";
import { Swiper, SwiperSlide } from "swiper/react";
import { Navigation } from "swiper/modules";
import "swiper/css";
import "swiper/css/navigation";
import LeftArrowIcon from "./LeftArrowIcon";
import RightArrowIcon from "./RightArrowIcon";
import { useRef, useState } from "react";

const PerfectionSlider = () => {
  const prevRef = useRef(null);
  const nextRef = useRef(null);
  const [progressIndex, setProgressIndex] = useState(0);

  return (
    <section
      id="perfection-slider-section"
      className="bg-black h-screen relative flex items-center justify-center"
    >
      <Swiper
        slidesPerView={4}
        spaceBetween={40}
        modules={[Navigation]}
        navigation={{
          prevEl: prevRef.current,
          nextEl: nextRef.current,
        }}
        onBeforeInit={(swiper) => {
          swiper.params.navigation.prevEl = prevRef.current;
          swiper.params.navigation.nextEl = nextRef.current;
        }}
        onSlideChange={(swiper) => {
          // index changes each time user slides
          setProgressIndex(swiper.activeIndex);
        }}
        className="mySwiper w-[80%]"
      >
        {Array.from({ length: 8 }, (_, i) => (
          <SwiperSlide
            key={i}
            className="bg-white text-black flex items-center justify-center text-xl font-bold h-[300px]"
          >
            Slide {i + 1}
          </SwiperSlide>
        ))}
      </Swiper>

      {/* arrow and line div container */}
      <section className="w-full absolute bottom-0 left-0 h-[15%]">
        {/* arrow div container */}
        <div className="absolute top-1/2 left-[10%] -translate-y-1/2 flex items-center gap-3 z-10">
          <div ref={prevRef} className="cursor-pointer">
            <LeftArrowIcon />
          </div>
          <div ref={nextRef} className="cursor-pointer">
            <RightArrowIcon />
          </div>
        </div>

        {/* line progress container */}
        <div className="w-3/5 lg:inline md:inline hidden absolute h-px right-[5%] top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 bg-gray-600 overflow-hidden">
          {/* progress steps (5 parts) */}
          <div className="flex justify-between w-full">
            {[0, 1, 2, 3, 4].map((index) => (
              <div
                key={index}
                className={`h-[3px] transition-all duration-500 ${
                  progressIndex >= index ? "bg-white" : "bg-gray-600"
                }`}
                style={{
                  width: "20%",
                }}
              ></div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </section>
  );
};

export default PerfectionSlider;

🧠 Explanation:

  • Navigation:
    The prevRef and nextRef are connected properly in onBeforeInit so your arrows actually control the Swiper.

  • Progress Line:
    The line is divided into 5 equal sections (20% each).
    When you move the slide, progressIndex updates from Swiper’s activeIndex.

  • Active Step:
    Each section turns white (bg-white) as you progress through slides.

Let's fix that — here’s the updated and correct version 👇

jsx
"use client";
import { Swiper, SwiperSlide } from "swiper/react";
import { Navigation } from "swiper/modules";
import "swiper/css";
import "swiper/css/navigation";
import LeftArrowIcon from "./LeftArrowIcon";
import RightArrowIcon from "./RightArrowIcon";
import { useRef, useState } from "react";

const PerfectionSlider = () => {
  const prevRef = useRef(null);
  const nextRef = useRef(null);
  const [activeStep, setActiveStep] = useState(0);

  // total slides and visible slides
  const totalSlides = 8;
  const slidesPerView = 4;
  const totalSteps = Math.ceil(totalSlides / slidesPerView); // 2 views but you said 5 parts
  const steps = 5; // manually setting to 5 parts for your design

  return (
    <section
      id="perfection-slider-section"
      className="bg-black h-screen relative flex items-center justify-center"
    >
      <Swiper
        slidesPerView={4}
        spaceBetween={40}
        modules={[Navigation]}
        navigation={{
          prevEl: prevRef.current,
          nextEl: nextRef.current,
        }}
        onBeforeInit={(swiper) => {
          swiper.params.navigation.prevEl = prevRef.current;
          swiper.params.navigation.nextEl = nextRef.current;
        }}
        onSlideChange={(swiper) => {
          // move step per slide
          const index = swiper.activeIndex;
          const newStep = index % steps; // cycles through steps
          setActiveStep(newStep);
        }}
        className="mySwiper w-[80%]"
      >
        {Array.from({ length: 8 }, (_, i) => (
          <SwiperSlide
            key={i}
            className="bg-white text-black flex items-center justify-center text-xl font-bold h-[300px]"
          >
            Slide {i + 1}
          </SwiperSlide>
        ))}
      </Swiper>

      {/* arrow and line div container */}
      <section className="w-full absolute bottom-0 left-0 h-[15%]">
        {/* arrow div container */}
        <div className="absolute top-1/2 left-[10%] -translate-y-1/2 flex items-center gap-3 z-10">
          <div ref={prevRef} className="cursor-pointer">
            <LeftArrowIcon />
          </div>
          <div ref={nextRef} className="cursor-pointer">
            <RightArrowIcon />
          </div>
        </div>

        {/* line progress container */}
        <div className="w-3/5 lg:inline md:inline hidden absolute h-px right-[5%] top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 bg-gray-600 overflow-hidden">
          {/* progress divided into 5 parts */}
          <div className="flex justify-between w-full">
            {[0, 1, 2, 3, 4].map((index) => (
              <div
                key={index}
                className={`h-[3px] transition-all duration-500 ${
                  activeStep === index ? "bg-white" : "bg-gray-600"
                }`}
                style={{
                  width: "20%",
                }}
              ></div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </section>
  );
};

export default PerfectionSlider;

🧩 What’s Changed:

  • Only one part of the 5-section line becomes white — the rest remain gray.

  • Each arrow click (slide change) updates the activeStep to a new segment.

  • You can easily customize the number of visible slides (slidesPerView) and number of parts (steps).

That will make it more visually aligned with your “4 visible per view” idea.

Ah, you want responsive breakpoints so that:

  • Mobile / small screens (<768px) → 1 slide per view

  • Medium / tablets (≥768px) → 4 slides per view

  • Large / desktop (≥1024px) → 4 slides per view

Right now your Swiper does not have breakpoints — you can add them using the breakpoints prop.

Here’s how to integrate it into your current code:

jsx
<Swiper
  slidesPerView={4} // default
  spaceBetween={40}
  modules={[Navigation]}
  navigation={{
    prevEl: prevRef.current,
    nextEl: nextRef.current,
  }}
  onBeforeInit={(swiper) => {
    swiper.params.navigation.prevEl = prevRef.current;
    swiper.params.navigation.nextEl = nextRef.current;
  }}
  onSlideChange={(swiper) => {
    const index = swiper.activeIndex;
    const newStep = index % steps;
    setActiveStep(newStep);
  }}
  breakpoints={{
    0: {
      slidesPerView: 1,
      spaceBetween: 20,
    },
    768: {
      slidesPerView: 4,
      spaceBetween: 40,
    },
    1024: {
      slidesPerView: 4,
      spaceBetween: 50,
    },
  }}
  className="mySwiper w-[80%]"
>
  {Array.from({ length: 8 }, (_, i) => {
    const data = fakeData[i % fakeData.length];
    return (
      <SwiperSlide key={i} className="relative group overflow-hidden rounded-xl h-[300px]">
        {/* Slide content */}
      </SwiperSlide>
    );
  })}
</Swiper>

✅ Notes:

  • breakpoints keys are minimum width in px.

  • Below 768px → 1 slide

  • From 768px → 4 slides

  • From 1024px → 4 slides (you can increase spacing if you want)

Ah! I see exactly what’s happening 😅

The reason your Swiper still shows 4 slides on small devices is because of how you set slidesPerView:

jsx
<Swiper
  slidesPerView={4} // ❌ this is the default, so it takes precedence
  breakpoints={{
    0: { slidesPerView: 1, spaceBetween: 20 },
    768: { slidesPerView: 4, spaceBetween: 40 },
    1024: { slidesPerView: 4, spaceBetween: 50 },
  }}
>

  • slidesPerView={4} is the default.

  • Swiper uses the default unless the viewport matches a breakpoint ≥ the key.

  • 0 is fine, but sometimes with Navigation enabled, Swiper might not correctly read prevEl/nextEl until after first render, so default can take over.

✅ Fix: remove the default slidesPerView={4} and only use breakpoints:

jsx
<Swiper
  // slidesPerView={4} ❌ remove this
  spaceBetween={40}
  modules={[Navigation]}
  navigation={{
    prevEl: prevRef.current,
    nextEl: nextRef.current,
  }}
  onBeforeInit={(swiper) => {
    swiper.params.navigation.prevEl = prevRef.current;
    swiper.params.navigation.nextEl = nextRef.current;
  }}
  breakpoints={{
    0: { slidesPerView: 1, spaceBetween: 20 },
    768: { slidesPerView: 4, spaceBetween: 40 },
    1024: { slidesPerView: 4, spaceBetween: 50 },
  }}
>

💡 Optional: force Swiper to recalc after render (common in Next.js with useRef navigation):

jsx
useEffect(() => {
  if (swiperRef.current) swiperRef.current.update();
}, []);

Ah! I see exactly what’s happening. This is a classic Swiper + React issue:

When you pass prevEl and nextEl to Swiper before the refs are mounted, Swiper doesn’t know the DOM elements yet. That’s why your arrows don’t work on first render, but work after you interact.

The solution is to use useEffect to initialize the navigation after the refs are set.

Here’s the fixed version of your component:

jsx
"use client";
import { Swiper, SwiperSlide } from "swiper/react";
import { Navigation } from "swiper/modules";
import "swiper/css";
import "swiper/css/navigation";
import LeftArrowIcon from "./LeftArrowIcon";
import RightArrowIcon from "./RightArrowIcon";
import { useRef, useState, useEffect } from "react";

const fakeData = [
  {
    image: "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1600585154340-be6161a56a0c",
    Orientation: "South Facing",
    Address: "123 Sunset Blvd, Dhaka",
    LandSize: "10 Katha",
    ApartmentSize: "2400 sq.ft",
    Units: 8,
    Parks: 2,
    Slots: 4,
  },
  {
    image: "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1580587771525-78b9dba3b914",
    Orientation: "East Facing",
    Address: "45 Green Road, Dhaka",
    LandSize: "8 Katha",
    ApartmentSize: "1800 sq.ft",
    Units: 6,
    Parks: 1,
    Slots: 3,
  },
  {
    image: "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1600607687939-ce8a6c25118c",
    Orientation: "North Facing",
    Address: "12 Gulshan Ave, Dhaka",
    LandSize: "12 Katha",
    ApartmentSize: "3000 sq.ft",
    Units: 10,
    Parks: 3,
    Slots: 5,
  },
  {
    image: "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1599423300746-b62533397364",
    Orientation: "West Facing",
    Address: "88 Banani, Dhaka",
    LandSize: "6 Katha",
    ApartmentSize: "1600 sq.ft",
    Units: 5,
    Parks: 1,
    Slots: 2,
  },
];

const PerfectionSlider = () => {
  const prevRef = useRef(null);
  const nextRef = useRef(null);
  const swiperRef = useRef(null);
  const [activeStep, setActiveStep] = useState(0);

  const steps = 5;

  // Initialize navigation after refs are mounted
  useEffect(() => {
    if (swiperRef.current && prevRef.current && nextRef.current) {
      swiperRef.current.params.navigation.prevEl = prevRef.current;
      swiperRef.current.params.navigation.nextEl = nextRef.current;
      swiperRef.current.navigation.init();
      swiperRef.current.navigation.update();
    }
  }, []);

  return (
    <section
      id="perfection-slider-section"
      className="bg-black h-screen relative flex items-center justify-center"
    >
      <Swiper
        onSwiper={(swiper) => (swiperRef.current = swiper)}
        modules={[Navigation]}
        onSlideChange={(swiper) => {
          const index = swiper.activeIndex;
          const newStep = index % steps;
          setActiveStep(newStep);
        }}
        breakpoints={{
          0: { slidesPerView: 1, spaceBetween: 20 },
          768: { slidesPerView: 4, spaceBetween: 40 },
          1024: { slidesPerView: 4, spaceBetween: 50 },
        }}
      >
        {Array.from({ length: 8 }, (_, i) => {
          const data = fakeData[i % fakeData.length];
          return (
            <SwiperSlide key={i} className="relative group overflow-hidden rounded-xl">
              <img
                src={data.image}
                alt={data.Address}
                className="w-full h-full object-cover transition-transform duration-700 group-hover:scale-110"
              />
              <div className="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-full h-full bg-black/60 translate-y-full group-hover:translate-y-0 transition-transform duration-700 flex flex-col justify-start p-5 text-white">
                <ul className="text-sm space-y-2">
                  {Object.entries(data).map(([key, value]) => {
                    if (key === "image") return null;
                    return (
                      <li key={key} className="flex items-center gap-2">
                        <span className="w-3 h-3 bg-white inline-block"></span>
                        <strong>{key.replace(/([A-Z])/g, " $1")}:</strong> {value}
                      </li>
                    );
                  })}
                </ul>
              </div>
            </SwiperSlide>
          );
        })}
      </Swiper>

      {/* Arrows + Progress Line */}
      <section className="w-full absolute bottom-0 left-0 h-[15%]">
        <div className="absolute top-1/2 left-[10%] -translate-y-1/2 flex items-center gap-3 z-10">
          <div ref={prevRef} className="cursor-pointer">
            <LeftArrowIcon />
          </div>
          <div ref={nextRef} className="cursor-pointer">
            <RightArrowIcon />
          </div>
        </div>

        <div className="w-3/5 lg:inline md:inline hidden absolute h-px right-[5%] top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 bg-gray-600 overflow-hidden">
          <div className="flex justify-between w-full">
            {[0, 1, 2, 3, 4].map((index) => (
              <div
                key={index}
                className={`h-[3px] transition-all duration-500 ${
                  activeStep === index ? "bg-white" : "bg-gray-600"
                }`}
                style={{ width: "20%" }}
              ></div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </section>
  );
};

export default PerfectionSlider;

✅ Key Fix:

  • Added swiperRef with onSwiper callback.

  • After the component mounts (useEffect), init and update the navigation so arrows work immediately.
